1
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:13,033
<i>Ashley shouldn't get dragged
into the mess her mom made.</i>

2
00:00:13,167 --> 00:00:14,967
<i> She'll be safer with us.</i>

3
00:00:15,100 --> 00:00:17,633
<i>Her future will be more
secure if she lives with us.</i>

4
00:00:17,767 --> 00:00:19,733
<i>I didn't realize you cared
that much,</i>

5
00:00:19,867 --> 00:00:21,333
<i> about Ashley's welfare.</i>

6
00:00:21,467 --> 00:00:22,700
<i> Remember Xander?</i>

7
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:24,633
<i>It's his birthday
countdown party later.</i>

8
00:00:24,767 --> 00:00:25,867
<i> Could I go?</i>

9
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,333
<i>I don't want you hanging
out,</i>

10
00:00:27,467 --> 00:00:30,033
<i>with bad influences like Xander.</i>

11
00:00:30,167 --> 00:00:31,267
<i> If I were you,</i>

12
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:34,567
<i>I'd go to the party just to show
them I'm responsible.</i>

13
00:00:34,733 --> 00:00:37,700
<i>Maybe then they won't be
so strict and controlling.</i>

14
00:00:37,833 --> 00:00:40,233
<i>Ashley, do you even know how
hard it is,</i>

15
00:00:40,367 --> 00:00:42,267
<i>to fight for our place
in this house?</i>

16
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:44,767
<i>You should focus on being
an academic achiever.</i>

17
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:46,267
<i>How many times has
this happened, Edward?</i>

18
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:49,367
<i>If you mess up again,
you're on your own.</i>

19
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:51,400
<i>I just wish I could feel
like I'm actually your son.</i>

20
00:00:51,533 --> 00:00:53,933
<i>Not just some project
you need to fix.</i>

21
00:00:54,067 --> 00:00:56,933
<i>Not just a list of mistakes
you're trying to correct.</i>

22
00:01:09,100 --> 00:01:10,067
Dad...

23
00:01:12,233 --> 00:01:18,500
Why is Grandfather like that
with you?

24
00:01:18,633 --> 00:01:20,033
Ashley,

25
00:01:20,167 --> 00:01:22,667
that's just how he is sometimes.

26
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:26,033
He praises one of his kids...

27
00:01:26,167 --> 00:01:27,867
and scolds the other.

28
00:01:29,367 --> 00:01:30,500
I'm the second kind.

29
00:01:32,167 --> 00:01:33,667
But it's fine.

30
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:36,733
I can handle it as long as,

31
00:01:36,867 --> 00:01:38,300
you and your mom are safe.

32
00:01:40,133 --> 00:01:41,500
But Dad...

33
00:01:43,433 --> 00:01:45,567
are we really safe here?

34
00:01:47,867 --> 00:01:48,733
It just...

35
00:01:50,033 --> 00:01:51,933
feels different back when we
were only staying overnight,

36
00:01:52,067 --> 00:01:55,467
compared to now that we actually
live here.

37
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:57,333
Of course, dear.

38
00:01:57,467 --> 00:01:59,233
You're more secure here.

39
00:01:59,367 --> 00:02:00,933
At least here,

40
00:02:01,067 --> 00:02:03,567
you get to eat whatever you
want, right?

41
00:02:03,700 --> 00:02:06,433
And you're with your cousin.

42
00:02:06,567 --> 00:02:08,667
Most importantly,

43
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,200
your mom is happy.

44
00:02:12,467 --> 00:02:13,467
Just...

45
00:02:14,667 --> 00:02:15,900
be strong, okay?

46
00:02:18,467 --> 00:02:21,100
Now that we live in this house,

47
00:02:21,233 --> 00:02:23,533
even the smallest mistake gets
marked against you.

48
00:02:24,567 --> 00:02:25,900
It's like,

49
00:02:26,033 --> 00:02:27,533
there are no second chances.

50
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:31,433
That's what it means to be a
Torrecampo,

51
00:02:31,567 --> 00:02:33,033
living under this roof.

52
00:02:35,100 --> 00:02:35,900
Yes, Dad.

53
00:03:39,733 --> 00:03:41,500
I'll find a way.

54
00:03:41,633 --> 00:03:43,667
I already told Kurt
I'd be there.

55
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:44,767
See you at the party!

56
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:46,267
I'm so excited!

57
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:49,167
Jasmine, what do you
mean you'll be there?

58
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:51,500
Since when did you
start defying me?

59
00:03:52,567 --> 00:03:53,967
Why are you listening in?

60
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:57,233
Are you monitoring my
phone calls now, too?

61
00:04:00,067 --> 00:04:01,833
Don't change the subject.

62
00:04:01,967 --> 00:04:04,000
Your dad and I already said no.

63
00:04:04,133 --> 00:04:06,900
So why are you still planning
to go?

64
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:09,367
I don't want to disobey you,
Mom.

65
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:11,233
I just want to do,

66
00:04:11,367 --> 00:04:13,067
what I want for once.

67
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:14,933
Why does Ashley's dad allow her,

68
00:04:15,067 --> 00:04:16,333
to do something when she wants
to?

69
00:04:16,467 --> 00:04:18,433
Your cousin isn't sick.

70
00:04:18,567 --> 00:04:20,000
You have a different condition.

71
00:04:20,133 --> 00:04:22,500
You need to be monitored.

72
00:04:22,633 --> 00:04:23,733
But Mom, I'm not fragile.

73
00:04:23,867 --> 00:04:25,667
I don't need to be protected all
the time.

74
00:04:28,167 --> 00:04:30,167
Aunt Thea's right.

75
00:04:30,300 --> 00:04:31,567
Maybe I should do something,

76
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:33,567
so you'll change the way
you see me.

77
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:37,500
What did your
Aunt Thea tell you?

78
00:04:39,267 --> 00:04:42,033
She said if I show you I
can handle things,

79
00:04:42,167 --> 00:04:44,000
maybe you won't worry so much.

80
00:04:47,767 --> 00:04:49,767
She was just trying
to help, Mom.

81
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:55,433
Mom, Mom, please! No!

82
00:04:55,567 --> 00:04:59,067
Mommy! Mom, Stop it! Stop!

83
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,567
One more.

84
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:04,467
Don't copy my smile,
show your teeth.

85
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,833
Smile properly, why is your
smile so stiff?

86
00:05:05,967 --> 00:05:07,600
Okay.

87
00:05:07,733 --> 00:05:09,200
Fix your hair, here, fix it.

88
00:05:09,333 --> 00:05:10,467
Mom, please stop!

89
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:11,567
Mom!

90
00:05:11,700 --> 00:05:12,667
Thea!

91
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:14,033
What's the truth?

92
00:05:14,167 --> 00:05:15,500
Why did you suddenly think
it was okay,

93
00:05:15,633 --> 00:05:17,633
to influence my daughter?

94
00:05:17,767 --> 00:05:19,767
Marj, what is this?

95
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:22,000
Don't act innocent.

96
00:05:22,133 --> 00:05:24,133
You were there when I told
her she couldn't go,

97
00:05:24,267 --> 00:05:27,367
and then you told her she should
go anyway?

98
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:30,333
Why are you undermining
my decision as a mother?

99
00:05:30,467 --> 00:05:33,133
Marj, I just feel sorry
for your daughter!

100
00:05:33,267 --> 00:05:34,167
She's suffocating!

101
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:36,600
She's like a prisoner
in her own house!

102
00:05:37,633 --> 00:05:39,833
Prisoner? Nobody's imprisoned
here!

103
00:05:39,967 --> 00:05:44,067
And who are you to interfere
with how I raise my child?

104
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:45,767
Mom, please stop.

105
00:05:45,900 --> 00:05:48,900
Please, let's
just talk calmly.

106
00:05:49,033 --> 00:05:51,900
I've been trying to understand
you and your family,

107
00:05:52,033 --> 00:05:55,033
but this is different when it
comes to my daughter!

108
00:05:55,167 --> 00:05:59,233
If I catch you again teaching my
child to disobey me,

109
00:05:59,367 --> 00:06:01,533
I will not hold back!

110
00:06:01,667 --> 00:06:04,667
Oh, really? And who are you to
threaten me?

111
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:06,833
You don't get to
dictate my life, Marj!

112
00:06:06,967 --> 00:06:08,433
You're really pushing me!

113
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,300
- Mommy!
- You're going too far!

114
00:06:10,433 --> 00:06:12,200
- You're blaming me?
- You've got some nerve!

115
00:06:14,267 --> 00:06:15,200
You have no right!

116
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:16,633
I have every right
in this house!

117
00:06:16,767 --> 00:06:19,333
Remember that!

118
00:06:19,467 --> 00:06:21,833
But you have no right
to my child!

119
00:06:23,033 --> 00:06:25,800
What is all this shouting?

120
00:06:25,933 --> 00:06:27,033
What is wrong with you?

121
00:06:27,167 --> 00:06:28,733
You sound like a bunch of
vendors fighting in the market!

122
00:06:28,867 --> 00:06:29,800
Don't you hear yourselves?

123
00:06:29,933 --> 00:06:32,400
Oh my gosh, this
is embarrassing!

124
00:06:32,533 --> 00:06:33,433
Mom.

125
00:06:33,567 --> 00:06:35,600
Mom.

126
00:06:35,733 --> 00:06:38,400
Marj started it, Mom.

127
00:06:38,533 --> 00:06:41,000
I was just trying to console
Jasmine,

128
00:06:41,167 --> 00:06:42,867
but she took it the wrong way.

129
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,367
Console?

130
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:46,200
Don't play innocent!

131
00:06:46,333 --> 00:06:49,267
Not only are you putting
my daughter at risk,

132
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:51,533
but you're disrespecting me
as her mother.

133
00:06:51,667 --> 00:06:54,233
How would you feel if
I did that to Ashley?

134
00:06:54,367 --> 00:06:56,167
Marj, calm down.

135
00:06:56,300 --> 00:06:57,700
You don't have
to make a scene.

136
00:06:57,833 --> 00:07:00,500
Maybe you could talk
to Thea peacefully.

137
00:07:00,633 --> 00:07:04,400
It's hard to stay calm
when she wants to harm my child!

138
00:07:04,533 --> 00:07:07,333
Excuse me? You're the one
complaining!

139
00:07:07,467 --> 00:07:10,567
- You've got some nerve!
- Silence!

140
00:07:15,667 --> 00:07:18,900
If you want to live under
one roof,

141
00:07:19,033 --> 00:07:21,567
learn to adjust.

142
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:24,833
Learn some humility, otherwise,
go your separate ways.

143
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:27,867
I don't want this
to happen again.

144
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,333
Not under my watch.

145
00:07:29,467 --> 00:07:30,733
Not in front of your daughters.

146
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:32,600
Do we understand each other?

147
00:07:36,167 --> 00:07:37,467
Yes, Mom.

148
00:07:39,100 --> 00:07:40,333
I'm sorry.

149
00:07:41,867 --> 00:07:43,533
I was just trying to help.

150
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:47,933
Let's not blow this
up any further.

151
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:50,400
And don't let Greg hear
about this.

152
00:07:56,567 --> 00:07:59,267
This ends now.

153
00:08:19,133 --> 00:08:20,433
Love,

154
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,233
calm down.

155
00:08:22,367 --> 00:08:24,600
I understand why you got mad.

156
00:08:24,733 --> 00:08:27,067
What Thea did was wrong.

157
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:29,533
I've been trying my best
to tolerate that woman,

158
00:08:29,667 --> 00:08:30,600
to avoid conflict.

159
00:08:30,733 --> 00:08:32,367
But now she's pulling
something again,

160
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:34,733
and our daughter's listening
to her.

161
00:08:34,867 --> 00:08:38,067
Love, I don't even know
how to protect our child,

162
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:40,700
when someone like her is living
in the same house.

163
00:08:42,933 --> 00:08:44,933
Love what if,

164
00:08:45,067 --> 00:08:46,633
we just take a breath?

165
00:08:46,767 --> 00:08:47,867
Let's go out.

166
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,200
Just the two of us.

167
00:08:50,733 --> 00:08:54,667
This isn't really the best
timing.

168
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:57,167
That's exactly why we should go.

169
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:01,600
You know what? We need a
breather from this house.

170
00:09:01,733 --> 00:09:03,767
You need a breather.

171
00:09:03,900 --> 00:09:06,133
Especially after what
happened earlier.

172
00:09:13,267 --> 00:09:15,233
Love,

173
00:09:15,367 --> 00:09:17,400
I'm not forcing you.

174
00:09:17,533 --> 00:09:19,600
But trust me.

175
00:09:19,733 --> 00:09:21,800
This will be good for you.

176
00:09:21,933 --> 00:09:23,067
For us.

177
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:40,667
Jasmine,

178
00:09:42,300 --> 00:09:47,567
before your dad and I leave, I
just want to say something.

179
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:52,067
I'm sorry if I've been
too strict lately.

180
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:54,733
I'm not doing it to...

181
00:09:54,867 --> 00:09:59,033
make your life hard, or because
I don't want you to be happy.

182
00:09:59,167 --> 00:10:01,700
I'm just worried
about your safety.

183
00:10:01,867 --> 00:10:06,333
Sometimes I can't help
being overly strict.

184
00:10:06,467 --> 00:10:08,867
Just be patient a little longer,
okay?

185
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:12,933
Once you're stronger, and once
the doctor says you're ready,

186
00:10:13,067 --> 00:10:16,900
you'll be able to do everything
you want.

187
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:18,433
But for now,

188
00:10:18,567 --> 00:10:21,233
please listen to me.

189
00:10:21,367 --> 00:10:23,300
I understand, Mom.

190
00:10:23,433 --> 00:10:24,567
It's okay.

191
00:10:24,700 --> 00:10:26,500
I'll just rest.

192
00:10:29,700 --> 00:10:31,733
Your dad and I are just
stepping out for dinner.

193
00:10:31,867 --> 00:10:33,533
We'll be back soon.

194
00:10:33,667 --> 00:10:37,200
If you need anything,
call me anytime.

195
00:10:37,367 --> 00:10:39,500
- Okay?
- Yes.

196
00:10:39,633 --> 00:10:41,433
- Okay, I love you.
- Love you.

197
00:10:41,567 --> 00:10:42,733
Good night.

198
00:10:42,867 --> 00:10:44,400
Good night, baby.

199
00:10:44,533 --> 00:10:45,667
Good night, Mom.

200
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:46,933
Enjoy.

201
00:11:34,867 --> 00:11:35,333
Thank you.

202
00:11:35,467 --> 00:11:36,033
You're welcome, sir.

203
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:42,567
Love, it's been so long
since we've been here.

204
00:11:42,733 --> 00:11:45,400
You remember.

205
00:11:45,533 --> 00:11:47,100
Did you know this is where
we had dinner

206
00:11:47,233 --> 00:11:48,600
on our first anniversary?

207
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:53,767
I just wanted to relive
when it was just us.

208
00:11:54,967 --> 00:11:56,600
When things weren't
this complicated.

209
00:11:57,733 --> 00:11:58,667
No pressure.

210
00:12:00,033 --> 00:12:02,833
We had pressure back then, too.

211
00:12:02,967 --> 00:12:03,967
Yeah.

212
00:12:04,867 --> 00:12:07,533
But it wasn't as serious
as the challenges now.

213
00:12:08,633 --> 00:12:12,067
Back then,
whenever we had issues,

214
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:18,667
I could fix them with my charm
and my good looks.

215
00:12:18,833 --> 00:12:19,967
But now...

216
00:12:20,967 --> 00:12:24,600
You're still ridiculously
charming and handsome.

217
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:26,733
And you fell in love
with me all over again.

218
00:12:32,267 --> 00:12:34,700
Good thing I came with you.

219
00:12:34,833 --> 00:12:36,567
I've missed us like this.

220
00:12:38,167 --> 00:12:39,300
Thank you, love.

221
00:12:40,367 --> 00:12:41,333
Really.

222
00:13:01,300 --> 00:13:02,300
Ash.

223
00:13:02,433 --> 00:13:04,067
Ash, wake up.

224
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,033
Ash, hurry.

225
00:13:05,167 --> 00:13:06,333
Wake up.

226
00:13:06,467 --> 00:13:07,567
Ashley!

227
00:13:09,433 --> 00:13:10,267
Wake up.

228
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:11,467
Hurry up.

229
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:18,700
Come on.

230
00:13:20,467 --> 00:13:21,333
Jas.

231
00:13:22,967 --> 00:13:24,067
What's going on?

232
00:13:24,633 --> 00:13:25,900
Come with me.

233
00:13:27,133 --> 00:13:28,233
What?

234
00:13:29,233 --> 00:13:31,767
Didn't your mom already
forbid you, Jas?

235
00:13:31,900 --> 00:13:34,300
And it's late.

236
00:13:34,433 --> 00:13:35,967
My parents aren't home.

237
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:37,733
We'll just be quick.

238
00:13:37,867 --> 00:13:39,233
We'll be back right away.

239
00:13:39,367 --> 00:13:41,000
No one will even know we left.

240
00:13:41,133 --> 00:13:42,300
Promise.

241
00:13:42,433 --> 00:13:44,500
We can't, Jas.

242
00:13:44,633 --> 00:13:46,167
They'll notice.

243
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:48,000
There's Manang.

244
00:13:48,133 --> 00:13:49,633
And there's CCTV downstairs.

245
00:13:50,700 --> 00:13:51,900
- What if--
- You think...

246
00:13:52,033 --> 00:13:53,100
this is my first time
sneaking out?

247
00:13:55,067 --> 00:13:56,633
But I'm bringing you this time

248
00:13:56,767 --> 00:13:59,500
because I know you need this,
too.

249
00:13:59,633 --> 00:14:01,333
Jas, we really can't.

250
00:14:01,467 --> 00:14:03,233
Look, cuz.

251
00:14:03,367 --> 00:14:05,200
I know we're both stressed,

252
00:14:05,333 --> 00:14:07,933
because our moms are extra
strict lately.

253
00:14:08,067 --> 00:14:10,700
I just want to
forget the pressure.

254
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:12,367
Even for one night.

255
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:14,033
We both need this.

256
00:14:15,467 --> 00:14:16,933
Come on.

257
00:14:17,067 --> 00:14:18,267
Just for a bit.

258
00:14:21,467 --> 00:14:24,233
One moment with no drama.

259
00:14:24,367 --> 00:14:25,700
No rules.

260
00:14:25,833 --> 00:14:27,500
No expectations.

261
00:14:27,633 --> 00:14:29,100
No moms.

262
00:14:32,067 --> 00:14:33,900
If you really don't want
to go,

263
00:14:34,033 --> 00:14:36,467
I'll just go by myself.

264
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:38,900
It's just that,

265
00:14:39,033 --> 00:14:41,833
no one will be there to help me
if something bad happens.

266
00:14:50,833 --> 00:14:53,533
Remember when that stage
logo almost fell on you?

267
00:14:53,667 --> 00:14:57,800
You were just standing there,
frozen.

268
00:14:57,933 --> 00:15:00,667
If I hadn't pulled you away,

269
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:03,267
you probably wouldn't have met,

270
00:15:03,433 --> 00:15:04,900
the man of your dreams.

271
00:15:10,233 --> 00:15:11,867
Love...

272
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:15,167
is everything okay?

273
00:15:15,300 --> 00:15:18,200
I was just checking
if Jasmine texted.

274
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:20,200
In case she needs something.

275
00:15:20,333 --> 00:15:22,067
Sorry, love.

276
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:25,933
Marj, maybe we can let Yolly
handle her tonight.

277
00:15:26,067 --> 00:15:30,167
Tonight, can we just pretend
you're Miss Tough Girl again,

278
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:31,900
and I'm your Prince Charming?

279
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:35,700
Love, remember the advice
I gave you before?

280
00:15:35,867 --> 00:15:37,300
Just let loose.

281
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:41,733
I'm really trying my best.

282
00:15:42,933 --> 00:15:47,533
I just feel guilty that
we didn't let Jasmine go.

283
00:15:47,667 --> 00:15:49,867
It seemed really important
to her.

284
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:54,033
What if we let her go and
we drive her ourselves?

285
00:15:54,167 --> 00:15:57,533
That way, we can make sure
nothing crazy happens.

286
00:15:57,667 --> 00:15:59,967
Oh, come on, love.

287
00:16:00,100 --> 00:16:02,533
I thought we were
having a good time.

288
00:16:02,667 --> 00:16:04,033
And now,

289
00:16:04,167 --> 00:16:05,533
you want to cut this short,

290
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,700
so we can chaperone Jas,

291
00:16:09,867 --> 00:16:11,400
at a party?

292
00:16:13,833 --> 00:16:15,067
Love.

293
00:16:18,033 --> 00:16:19,133
Waiter.

294
00:16:22,667 --> 00:16:24,467
Bill, please.

295
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:25,800
Paolo,

296
00:16:25,933 --> 00:16:27,633
You want to go home already,
don't you?

297
00:16:27,767 --> 00:16:29,033
Fine, let's go.

298
00:16:44,133 --> 00:16:45,333
<i> Jas?</i>

299
00:16:46,767 --> 00:16:48,333
Jasmine?

300
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:54,200
Here are your vitamins.

301
00:16:54,333 --> 00:16:55,767
Go ahead and take them.

302
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,433
Jas, why are you under
the covers?

303
00:17:01,567 --> 00:17:03,133
Aren't you feeling hot?

304
00:17:22,633 --> 00:17:23,967
Hello, Ma'am. Sir.

305
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:27,167
If you were just forcing
yourself to come,

306
00:17:27,300 --> 00:17:29,400
you shouldn't have done it in
the first place.

307
00:17:29,533 --> 00:17:30,800
Paolo, I showed up.

308
00:17:31,933 --> 00:17:33,667
You saw that I tried.

309
00:17:34,700 --> 00:17:36,267
Why can't you at least
appreciate that?

310
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,500
Love, it's not my fault
that I'm distracted

311
00:17:39,633 --> 00:17:42,100
after everything that happened
at the house today.

312
00:17:42,233 --> 00:17:43,933
You know what? Enough.

313
00:17:44,067 --> 00:17:46,133
Let's just end this night.

314
00:17:46,267 --> 00:17:48,233
Ma'am Marj!

315
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,267
Ma'am Marj!

316
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:50,633
Sir Paolo!

317
00:17:50,767 --> 00:17:52,367
It's Jasmine!

318
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:54,800
Jasmine is missing!

319
00:17:56,367 --> 00:17:57,800
My God, Jasmine.

320
00:18:02,133 --> 00:18:03,267
Where is this?

321
00:18:05,367 --> 00:18:06,567
I just talked to Weng earlier.

322
00:18:06,700 --> 00:18:08,867
She said Jasmine
was in bed, asleep.

323
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:10,733
Ma'am, she's not asleep.

324
00:18:10,867 --> 00:18:13,133
It was just a pillow
under the blanket.

325
00:18:13,267 --> 00:18:15,667
Jasmine is gone.

326
00:18:18,767 --> 00:18:20,667
Did you check the other rooms?

327
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:22,500
I've looked around
the house already.

328
00:18:22,667 --> 00:18:23,833
What about in Ashley's room?

329
00:18:34,533 --> 00:18:35,600
Jasmine.

330
00:18:36,267 --> 00:18:37,867
Jasmine, why do you keep
declining the calls?

331
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:40,333
What's wrong with you?

332
00:18:40,467 --> 00:18:41,200
Oh my God.

333
00:18:41,333 --> 00:18:43,100
Do you think they're
home already?

334
00:18:43,233 --> 00:18:44,133
That was fast.

335
00:18:45,067 --> 00:18:47,333
What if they know we're gone?

336
00:18:47,467 --> 00:18:49,933
Oh my God, Jasmine,
what if they know we sneak out?

337
00:18:50,067 --> 00:18:51,767
Why did you...

338
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:53,700
I'm trying to focus!

339
00:19:04,100 --> 00:19:05,967
Jasmine, it's your dad calling.

340
00:19:06,100 --> 00:19:08,933
- Can we just go back now.
- Ashley, calm down.

341
00:19:09,067 --> 00:19:10,733
We're seeing this through.

342
00:19:10,867 --> 00:19:12,900
If we're going to get yelled at
when we get home,

343
00:19:13,033 --> 00:19:14,000
then let's make it worth it.

344
00:19:14,133 --> 00:19:15,733
Let's at least enjoy
the party first.

345
00:19:15,867 --> 00:19:16,700
Okay?

346
00:19:16,833 --> 00:19:17,700
What?

347
00:19:19,933 --> 00:19:20,933
But Jas...

348
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:24,367
- what if they ground us?
- Ashley, please!

349
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:25,800
I'm trying to focus!

350
00:19:25,933 --> 00:19:28,367
But Jasmine, what if they
really get mad at us?

351
00:19:28,533 --> 00:19:29,667
Come on!

352
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:34,200
Can we just go home already?

353
00:19:34,333 --> 00:19:36,367
I'm done with this!

354
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:37,500
I'm done with this!

355
00:19:45,300 --> 00:19:46,167
Thea!

356
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:47,533
Thea!

357
00:19:47,667 --> 00:19:48,600
What is wrong with you people?

358
00:19:48,733 --> 00:19:50,600
Where's Jasmine?
Did she ask permission from you?

359
00:19:50,733 --> 00:19:52,100
Why are you asking me
where your daughter is?

360
00:19:52,233 --> 00:19:54,300
Didn't you tell me to
stay away from her?

361
00:19:54,433 --> 00:19:56,567
Just answer my question!

362
00:19:56,700 --> 00:19:59,167
I don't know where
your daughter is!

363
00:19:59,300 --> 00:20:01,400
The last time I talked
to her was this morning.

364
00:20:01,567 --> 00:20:03,233
Maybe she's in Ashley's room.

365
00:20:03,367 --> 00:20:04,533
She's not there.

366
00:20:04,667 --> 00:20:05,867
And Ashley's not there either.

367
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:07,167
What?

368
00:20:07,300 --> 00:20:08,333
That's impossible!

369
00:20:08,467 --> 00:20:11,100
Ashley never goes out
past her bedtime.

370
00:20:17,667 --> 00:20:19,100
What did your daughter do
to mine?

371
00:21:05,267 --> 00:21:06,333
Jasmine?

372
00:21:07,633 --> 00:21:08,867
Jasmine?

373
00:21:09,033 --> 00:21:09,933
Wake up, Jasmine.

374
00:21:10,067 --> 00:21:11,300
Are you okay?

375
00:21:30,033 --> 00:21:31,100
Help!

376
00:21:31,233 --> 00:21:32,800
Somebody help us!

377
00:21:34,833 --> 00:21:36,167
Jasmine.

378
00:21:36,300 --> 00:21:37,300
Jasmine, please wake up.

379
00:21:37,433 --> 00:21:39,433
Please, Jasmine.

380
00:21:39,567 --> 00:21:41,800
Jasmine, wake up, please.

381
00:22:04,933 --> 00:22:07,367
Jasmine, just hold on, okay?

382
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:10,233
We're getting help.

383
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:31,900
The other SUV's gone.

384
00:22:32,033 --> 00:22:33,367
And the spare key is missing.

385
00:22:33,500 --> 00:22:34,800
What?

386
00:22:34,933 --> 00:22:35,900
They don't even know
how to drive.

387
00:22:36,033 --> 00:22:39,067
What if something
happened to them?

388
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:40,167
Why would they do that?

389
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:42,600
Where would they even go?

390
00:22:42,733 --> 00:22:43,967
To Xander's party.

391
00:22:44,100 --> 00:22:46,133
Jasmine told me about
it this morning.

392
00:22:46,267 --> 00:22:48,333
That's probably where they went.

393
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:50,033
This is all your fault.

394
00:22:50,167 --> 00:22:51,400
You were too strict,

395
00:22:51,533 --> 00:22:54,233
that's why my granddaughter
rebelled and ran away like this!

396
00:22:55,567 --> 00:22:56,467
Enough, Regina!

397
00:22:58,133 --> 00:22:59,567
This is not the time
to blame anyone.

398
00:22:59,700 --> 00:23:02,633
We need to find the girls.

399
00:23:02,767 --> 00:23:03,467
Does the car have GPS?

400
00:23:03,600 --> 00:23:04,667
A tracking system?

401
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:05,833
Anything we can use?

402
00:23:10,300 --> 00:23:10,867
Hello?

403
00:23:12,467 --> 00:23:15,700
Yes, I'm Jasmine Torrecampo's
mother.

404
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:17,700
What?

405
00:23:17,833 --> 00:23:19,733
They were in an accident?

406
00:23:19,867 --> 00:23:20,800
What?

407
00:23:20,933 --> 00:23:22,600
- Greg.
- How are they?

408
00:23:22,767 --> 00:23:23,633
What happened?

409
00:23:23,767 --> 00:23:25,033
Which hospital?

410
00:23:25,167 --> 00:23:26,167
Hello?

411
00:23:41,267 --> 00:23:42,567
Nurse.

412
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:43,533
Are you the Torrecampo family?

413
00:23:43,667 --> 00:23:44,400
Yes. Where are they?

414
00:23:44,533 --> 00:23:45,467
What happened?

415
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:48,733
The two girls,
Jasmine and Ashley, are okay.

416
00:23:48,867 --> 00:23:50,867
But we still need
to monitor them.

417
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:52,367
Does Ashley have
any head injuries?

418
00:23:52,500 --> 00:23:54,433
Is she hurt?

419
00:23:54,567 --> 00:23:55,600
Just minor wounds.

420
00:23:55,767 --> 00:23:57,400
They're both stable.

421
00:23:57,533 --> 00:24:01,000
Jasmine was unconscious
when the ambulance arrived.

422
00:24:01,133 --> 00:24:03,600
She passed out?

423
00:24:03,733 --> 00:24:04,333
Why?

424
00:24:04,467 --> 00:24:05,033
How is she now?

425
00:24:05,167 --> 00:24:06,233
Is she awake?

426
00:24:06,367 --> 00:24:07,800
You just said she was stable!

427
00:24:07,933 --> 00:24:08,800
She's conscious now.

428
00:24:08,933 --> 00:24:10,467
We're just running tests

429
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:13,567
to make sure there are no
internal injuries.

430
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:14,567
Oh my God.

431
00:24:16,700 --> 00:24:17,700
Please wait for further updates.

432
00:24:21,233 --> 00:24:22,833
What were they thinking?

433
00:24:22,967 --> 00:24:24,100
Sneaking out like that!

434
00:24:25,367 --> 00:24:27,233
Ashley never even
causes trouble.

435
00:24:27,367 --> 00:24:28,700
My daughter got dragged
into this.

436
00:24:28,867 --> 00:24:30,633
What?

437
00:24:30,767 --> 00:24:32,067
Are you trying to
say something, Thea?

438
00:24:33,233 --> 00:24:35,333
Don't start.

439
00:24:35,467 --> 00:24:37,533
She's been talking nonstop,

440
00:24:37,667 --> 00:24:40,167
like she's implying Jasmine
wanted this to happen.

441
00:24:40,300 --> 00:24:42,500
Like my daughter's the only one
at fault.

442
00:24:42,633 --> 00:24:43,567
Hold on.

443
00:24:43,700 --> 00:24:45,433
We don't even know what
really happened yet.

444
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:46,500
Oh, really?

445
00:24:46,633 --> 00:24:48,033
Who was desperate to go out

446
00:24:48,167 --> 00:24:50,367
because she's constantly
forbidden from doing anything?

447
00:24:50,500 --> 00:24:51,967
My daughter is well-behaved.

448
00:24:52,100 --> 00:24:55,067
She doesn't go partying
unless your daughter,

449
00:24:55,200 --> 00:24:57,433
who never shuts up about wanting
to go out, drags her along!

450
00:25:02,167 --> 00:25:03,833
Jasmine would never have
thought about sneaking out

451
00:25:03,967 --> 00:25:05,600
if you hadn't fueled the idea!

452
00:25:05,733 --> 00:25:07,800
You should be grateful nothing
happened to my daughter.

453
00:25:07,933 --> 00:25:09,967
Because if it had,
I would've blamed you.

454
00:25:10,100 --> 00:25:10,867
Wow.

455
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:12,233
So now you're the righteous one?

456
00:25:12,367 --> 00:25:14,533
Fine. It's all our fault.

457
00:25:14,667 --> 00:25:16,333
That's your specialty, right?

458
00:25:16,467 --> 00:25:17,700
Blaming everyone.

459
00:25:17,833 --> 00:25:19,500
Playing the victim.

460
00:25:19,633 --> 00:25:22,800
But never seeing
your own mistakes.

461
00:25:22,933 --> 00:25:25,200
You just can't accept that
your daughter ran away

462
00:25:25,333 --> 00:25:27,267
because you're
over-the-top strict.

463
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:28,233
That's enough, Thea.

464
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:33,167
You know what? We're not getting
anywhere blaming each other.

465
00:25:34,900 --> 00:25:36,533
Marj, please don't engage.

466
00:25:36,700 --> 00:25:38,300
Let's just focus on Jasmine.

467
00:25:38,433 --> 00:25:39,533
She needs us right now.

468
00:25:39,667 --> 00:25:40,533
Okay?

469
00:25:41,933 --> 00:25:43,200
You can go in now.

470
00:25:43,333 --> 00:25:44,233
You can see them.

471
00:25:56,333 --> 00:25:58,367
Paolo, I need to understand.

472
00:25:58,500 --> 00:26:00,433
Why did you do this, Jas?

473
00:26:00,567 --> 00:26:01,667
You knew it was forbidden.

474
00:26:01,800 --> 00:26:03,000
You knew it was dangerous.

475
00:26:03,133 --> 00:26:04,967
Am I still the problem here?

476
00:26:05,100 --> 00:26:08,500
Aunt Marj, I was the one who
asked Jasmine to come with me.

477
00:26:08,667 --> 00:26:10,300
I thought you were a good kid.

478
00:26:10,433 --> 00:26:13,233
Turns out you're the bad
influence on my daughter.

479
00:26:13,367 --> 00:26:15,433
What were you thinking?

480
00:26:15,567 --> 00:26:18,867
Do you want your grandparents
to see you as a delinquent?

481
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:20,800
How are we supposed to earn
their trust

482
00:26:20,933 --> 00:26:22,567
if this is what you show them?

483
00:26:22,700 --> 00:26:23,967
So why did you do it?

484
00:26:24,100 --> 00:26:25,033
You said it yourself.

485
00:26:25,167 --> 00:26:26,300
That's what best friends do.

486
00:26:26,433 --> 00:26:28,300
We have each other's backs, Jas.

487
00:26:28,433 --> 00:26:29,667
And you're more than
a best friend to me.

488
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:30,933
You're like a sister.

489
00:26:31,067 --> 00:26:32,167
Oh my God, Jasmine!

490
00:26:32,300 --> 00:26:34,067
Your nose is bleeding!
